@node "OtherPrograms" "Other Programs"

  PPMS comes with a small program called 'Projects' which in short will
  display a directory list of a specified directory. It is mainly for
  the quick loading of projects directly to PPMS, however could be used
  for other purposes such as quickly viewing directories.

  TEMPLATE from CLI:
     D=DIR/K/A,F=FONT,FS=FONTSIZE/N,OP=OLDLOOKPROP/S,ML=MAXLINES/N,I=INDENT/S,NB=NOBACKFILL/S

  TOOLTYPES:
     DIR             Initial directory to look at
     FONT            Font to use
     FONTSIZE        Font size
     OLDLOOKPROP     By default uses a NEWLOOKPROP, set this to use shitty black one
     MAXLINES        Maximum number of lines in window
     INDENT          Set to indent instead of extrude the highlight box
     NOBACKFILL      Set to disable the backfill patttern

  To load a project highlight by moving the mouse over it and click.
  At present nothing but projects will do anything.

  To quit press the right mouse button.

@endnode

@node "Concept" "Concept"

  @{b}@{u}The concept of PPMS@{ub}@{uu}

  Programmers Project Management System (PPMS) is a complete system to create
  and manage projects by way of an easy to use GUI.

  After trying to maintain projects in the editors I usually use I found the
  following problems:
  - Alterations and management of makefiles becomes unbearable.
  - Selecting files in my projects to edit was a pain, having to load from
    a requester or equivilent.
  - Easily changing options for each source files or all of them was
    painful having to alter makefiles.
  - Debugging was difficult.
  - Error management had to be done through external programs.
  - Plenty of other problems which stemmed from these problems.
  - Some other project management programs were just too inflexable or
    unusable.


  So I decided to fix this once and for all...

  Here are some of PPMS's features:
  - Full project source files list manipulation.
  - Unlimited source files of any kind (C, Assembler, E, etc.)
  - Different compiling options for each source file.
  - File dependancies for each source file.
  - Ability to compile each source file to a seperate executable or
    seperately as one executable.
  - Compilation of source file currently being edited or
  - Project building of modified source files only or
  - Project building of all source files or
  - (Re)linking of project executable.
  - Ability to set executable file name for linked projects.
  - Customizable output (running or debugging) and compilation windows.
  - Multiple configurable translators (compilers, assemblers etc.)
  - Nested header checking for C source files.
  - Error parsing with warning suppression for each translator.
  - Full linker control.
  - Configurable linker lib modules.
  - Debugging control.
  - Full AREXX interface control.
  - Editor preferences allowing customization of any editor supporting
    AREXX so that the user can
    select the editor most suited to a project and be ready to program
    immediately.

@endnode

@node "Registration" "Registration"

  @{b}@{u}Registration@{ub}@{uu}

  This software is SHAREWARE and needs a keyfile to become completely
  functional. Without the keyfile PPMS is limited in several ways:
  · An about requester will appear occasionly.
  · A limit of 5 files per project.
  · Limited to one translator per project.
  · Boldface and italics disabled in output window which makes reading it
    more difficult and unpleasant.
  · BUILD ALL and BUILD FORCELINK disabled.
  · COMPILE disabled.
  · ERROR FIRST and ERROR PREVIOUS disabled.

