@node "Main Window" "Main Window"

  @{b}@{u}Main Window@{ub}@{uu}

  @{b}@{u}Folders:@{ub}@{uu}

   - Files
       The files listview contains the source files you want to be able to
       access. Thay don't neccissarily have to be compilable.
       Three columns are available:
   1. Files      - Files shown in bold have a translator so are
	 compilable.
	 Files shown in italics are not going to be compiled
	 when the project is built.
	 To make a file not compile double click on it's name
	 on the left column of the listview to toggle it
	 between italics (not compilable) and normal
	 (compilable) typefaces. Double clicking on a file
	 with no translator will do nothing.
   2. Options    - These are local compilation options for each source
	 file. To edit a files options double click on this
	 column and modify the string gadget which will
	 appear.
   3. Dependants - These are dependant files which will make the source
	 file compile if they are newer than the object file.
	 To add or remove dependant files double click on
	 this column and modify with the window which will
	 appear using the Add and Remove buttons.
       Add            - Add file(s) to the listview.
       Remove         - Remove file(s) from the listview.
       Edit           - Load file(s) from the listview to your chosen editor.
       Clear          - Clear all files from the listview.

   - Options
       Exe name          - Executable name for the project. There are the
	    following special tags:
	     %src     - the file currently being edited.
	     %mod     - the file currently being edited
		   without extension.
	     %base    - the file currently being edited
		   without extension or path.
	     %arg     - the arguments sent to the program when
		   run as below.
       Arguments         - The arguments for the executable. There are the
	    following special tags:
	     %src     - the file currently being edited.
	     %mod     - the file currently being edited
		   without extension.
	     %base    - the file currently being edited
		   without extension or path.
	     %screen  - the screen the editor is on.
       Output window     - The window or file you want the output of running
	    or debugging
	    to be sent to. If clear the default will be used.
       Compile window    - The window or file you want the output of
	    compilation or building
	    to be sent to. If clear the default will be used.
       Program dir       - The main directory of the project.
       Use debug options - Use debugging options for compilation and linking
	    or not.
       Linker            - Use the linker in building the project or not.
       Link all          - Link files with a translator but not compilable.
	    See the explanation of the Files list above.
       Requester         - Show a requester after compilation or building or
	    not.
       Make Window       - Open the building or compilation window or not.
       Run Window        - Open the run or debugging window or not.

   - Translators
       The listview shows the current translators in this project.
       Add               - Add a new translator.
       Delete            - Delete the active translator.

       Atributes:
    Command             - CLI Command to invoke the translator.
    Debug options       - Global options for source files in debug build
		mode.
    Final options       - Global options for source files in final build
		mode.
		Special tags for both of these are:
	     %src  - the source file
	     %mod  - the source file without extension
	     %base - the source file without extension or
		path
	     %opt  - the source file's local options
	     %obj  - the object file name
	     %mobj - the object file name with path and
		object directory
	     %bobj - the object file name without path
		and object directory

    Source extension(s) - Source file extensions for this translator.
		Multiple
		extensions may be defined be seperating with a
		comma. i.e.
		asm,s,a or .asm,.s,.a
    Object extension    - Extension of this translator file types
		object. i.e. o
		This is so PPMS can find the object files to
		compare dates
		with source files.
    Object directory    - The directory the object files are placed in
		or nothing.
    Ignore Warnings     - Not implemented yet.
    Check Headers       - Check source C files headers to see if they
		are newer than the source. This will only work
		for C files and checks all local
		#include "..." statements.

    Message converter:
      Select the message converter to use for your compiler.
      If you want to write your own converter these are the rules:
	They are standard executable programs called with the output of
	the compiler
	or assembler as an argument. They read the error file directly
	from stdin and write
	directly to stdout.
	Each error or warning has it's own line of the format:
	"#filename# line E|W number: message" where E|W is for Error or
	Warning (not both)

	for example an output for SAS/C might read:

	#helloworld.c# 1 E 4: invalid lexical token
	#helloworld.c# 5 W 73: declaration expected

	This means an error number 4 'invalid lexical token' was found
	at line 1 in helloworld.c and
	a warning number 5 'declaration expected' was found at line 5 in
	helloworld.c

   - Linker
       Command          - CLI Command to execute to invoke the linker.
       Object extension - The extension of the linkers object modules.
       Debug options    - Global options for linker in debug build mode.
       Final options    - Global options for linker in final build mode.
	    Special tags for both of these are:
	      %exe - Project executable name (from Options
		folder - Exe Name)
	      %lnk - File of objects to link with.
	      %obj - List of objects to link with.
	      %err - Error file to send output to.
	      %lib - Linker libs in listview.
       Linker libs:
    These are the libs the linker will link with.
    Add            - Add file(s) to list.
    Delete         - Delete file(s) from list.

   - Debugger
       Command - CLI Command to execute the debugger.
       Options - Options for the debugger. These are the special tags:
	 %exe    - Executable name.
	 %arg    - Executable arguments.
	 %src    - Current source file.
	 %mod    - Current source file without extension.
	 %base   - Current source file without extension or path.
	 %screen - Screen the editor is on.

  @{b}@{u}Buttons:@{ub}@{uu}

       New     - Clear everything for a new project to be set up.
       Load    - Load a project.
       Save    - Save this project.
       Save as - Ask for a name and save this project.

  @{b}@{u}Menus:@{ub}@{uu}

   @{u}PPMS@{uu}

   - New                - As with buttons above.
   - Load               - As with buttons above.
   - Save               - As with buttons above.
   - Save as            - As with buttons above.
   ----------
   - Editor Preferences - Go to editor preferences window.
   ----------
   - About...           - Display information about PPMS.
   - About MUI...       - Display information about MUI.
   ----------
   - Quit               - Quit PPMS.

   @{u}Project@{uu}

   - Compile            - Compile active source file.
   ---------------
   - Build              - Build project.
   - Build all          - Build all files in project.
   - Build forcelink    - Build project and force linker to run.
   ---------------
   - Debug              - Invoke debugger.
   - Run                - Run executable.

   @{u}Errors@{uu}

   - First              - Go to first error.
   - Next               - Go to next error.
   - Previous           - Go to previous error.

@endnode

