@node "Editors Window" "Editors Window"

  @{b}@{u}Editor preferences@{ub}@{uu}

  @{u}Editor@{uu}

    Editor name - Editor you are editing.
    Add         - Add a new editor.
    Remove      - Remove an editor.
    Editor path - Path of the editor so PPMS can invoke it if neccessary.
    ARexx port  - ARexx port to communicate with editor.
    Seperator   - Character to seperate seperate instances of the editor

  @{u}ARexx commands@{uu}

    Initial (lock) string - Command to lock editor. (optional)
			    Used when sending any other commands.
    Final (unlock) string - Command to unlock editor. (optional)
			    Used when sending any other commands.
    Standard messages     - Command to make editor show a message.
			    Used for errors.
    Audible messages      - Command to make editor show a message.
			    Used for major errors.
    Change directory      - Command to tell editor to change it's
			    current directory.
    Project clear         - Command to tell editor to clear it's
			    own project files list. (optional)
    Project add           - Command to add a file to editor's
			    project list.
    Open file(s)          - Command to tell editor to open file(s)
			    to edit.
    Query current file    - Command to get editor to give PPMS the
			    name of currently active file. Used for
			    compiling single files.
    Get editors pubscreen - Command to get editors screen.
    Save modified file(s) - Command to tell editor to save all
			    files that are modified.
    Goto file             - Command to tell editor to go to or open
			    if neccessary a file. Used for errors.
    Goto line             - Command to tell editor to go to a line
			    in a file. Used for errors.

  @{u}Buttons@{uu}

    OK     - Save all changes and return to main window.
    Cancel - Forget all changes and return to main window.




  Example editor preferences file is supplied with ARexx commands
  for GoldED.        
@endnode

